{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KwXRf2shz6wB7rGNLTaQDu","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t// The landing page served at / — framed as a short Wikipedia-style article: a\n2\t// lead paragraph, a catalogue infobox, a brief \"How to play\" block, and the\n3\t// puzzle picker as a dense, scannable table. Puzzle summaries are rendered\n4\t// server-side (no client fetch, no loading flash); the only client JS is the\n5\t// auth chip in the body header.\n6\timport type { PuzzleSummary } from \"./puzzles.js\";\n7\timport {\n8\t  AUTH_CHIP_SCRIPT,\n9\t  authChip,\n10\t  bodyHeader,\n11\t  escapeHtml,\n12\t  PAGE_CSS,\n13\t  pageHeader,\n14\t} from \"./ui.js\";\n15\t\n16\tconst DIFFICULTY_LABEL: Record<string, string> = {\n17\t  easy: \"Easy\",\n18\t  medium: \"Medium\",\n19\t  hard: \"Hard\",\n20\t};\n21\t\n22\t// Pull every 4-digit year out of the catalogue's per-puzzle span strings\n23\t// (\"1776–2007\", \"2001\", …) so the infobox can report the overall coverage.\n24\tfunction catalogueYears(puzzles: PuzzleSummary[]): number[] {\n25\t  return puzzles\n26\t    .flatMap((p) => p.span.split(/[^0-9]+/))\n27\t    .filter(Boolean)\n28\t    .map(Number);\n29\t}\n30\t\n31\texport function homepage({\n32\t  app,\n33\t  version,\n34\t  puzzles,\n35\t}: {\n36\t  app: string;\n37\t  version: string;\n38\t  puzzles: PuzzleSummary[];\n39\t}): string {\n40\t  const totalEvents = puzzles.reduce((n, p) => n + p.eventCount, 0);\n41\t  const years = catalogueYears(puzzles);\n42\t  const overallSpan = years.length\n43\t    ? `${Math.min(...years)}–${Math.max(...years)}`\n44\t    : \"—\";\n45\t  // Difficulties present, in canonical order, for the infobox range.\n46\t  const order = [\"easy\", \"medium\", \"hard\"];\n47\t  const diffs = order.filter((d) => puzzles.some((p) => p.difficulty === d));\n48\t  const diffRange = diffs.map((d) => DIFFICULTY_LABEL[d] ?? d).join(\" – \");\n49\t\n50\t  const rows = puzzles\n51\t    .map((p) => {\n52\t      const label = DIFFICULTY_LABEL[p.difficulty] ?? p.difficulty;\n53\t      const theme = p.theme ?? \"Mixed events\";\n54\t      return `\n55\t      <tr>\n56\t        <td><a href=\"/play/${escapeHtml(p.id)}\">${escapeHtml(theme)}</a></td>\n57\t        <td>${escapeHtml(label)}</td>\n58\t        <td>${p.eventCount}</td>\n59\t        <td>${escapeHtml(p.span)}</td>\n60\t      </tr>`;\n61\t    })\n62\t    .join(\"\");\n63\t\n64\t  return `<!doctype html>\n65\t<html lang=\"en\">\n66\t<head>\n67\t<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n68\t<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\">\n69\t<title>${escapeHtml(app)} — a history timeline placement game</title>\n70\t<style>\n71\t${PAGE_CSS}\n72\t  .infobox.cat{float:right;width:290px;max-width:46%;margin:.2rem 0 1rem 1.5rem}\n73\t  @media(max-width:640px){.infobox.cat{float:none;width:auto;max-width:none;margin:1rem 0}}\n74\t  .howto{margin:.4rem 0 0}\n75\t</style>\n76\t</head>\n77\t<body>\n78\t${pageHeader()}\n79\t${bodyHeader({\n80\t  left: \"A history timeline placement game\",\n81\t  right: `<a href=\"/openapi\">API</a>${authChip()}`,\n82\t})}\n83\t\n84\t<main class=\"wrap\">\n85\t  <article>\n86\t    <aside class=\"infobox cat\" aria-label=\"Catalogue summary\">\n87\t      <div class=\"ib-title\">${escapeHtml(app)}</div>\n88\t      <table>\n89\t        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Puzzles</th><td>${puzzles.length}</td></tr>\n90\t        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Events</th><td>${totalEvents}</td></tr>\n91\t        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Span</th><td>${escapeHtml(overallSpan)}</td></tr>\n92\t        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Difficulty</th><td>${escapeHtml(diffRange || \"—\")}</td></tr>\n93\t        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Source</th><td>Hand-authored, Wikipedia</td></tr>\n94\t      </table>\n95\t    </aside>\n96\t\n97\t    <p class=\"lead\">You are shown a historical event with its date hidden, and you\n98\t    slot it onto a shared timeline — before, after, or between the events already\n99\t    placed. Commit to reveal the real date, score the guess, and read more on\n100\t    Wikipedia. It is played in the spirit of the board game <i>Timeline</i>.</p>\n101\t\n102\t    <h2 id=\"how-to-play\">How to play</h2>\n103\t    <ol class=\"howto\">\n104\t      <li>Pick a puzzle from the table below.</li>\n105\t      <li>The board opens with one anchor event already placed and dated. Earlier\n106\t      events sit toward the top, later events toward the bottom.</li>\n107\t      <li>You are handed the rest one at a time, date hidden. Tap a marked gap, then\n108\t      tap Commit.</li>\n109\t      <li>Commit reveals the date. Correct earns 100 points plus a 25-point streak\n110\t      bonus per consecutive hit; wrong scores nothing and snaps into place. Either\n111\t      way the timeline stays in order.</li>\n112\t    </ol>\n113\t\n114\t    <h2 id=\"puzzles\">Puzzles</h2>\n115\t    <table class=\"wikitable\">\n116\t      <thead>\n117\t        <tr><th scope=\"col\">Puzzle</th><th scope=\"col\">Difficulty</th>\n118\t            <th scope=\"col\">Events</th><th scope=\"col\">Years</th></tr>\n119\t      </thead>\n120\t      <tbody>\n121\t        ${rows}\n122\t      </tbody>\n123\t    </table>\n124\t\n125\t    <p>This demo ships ${puzzles.length} hand-authored puzzles. The roadmap is puzzles\n126\t    generated on demand from Wikidata and Wikipedia, emitted against the same typed\n127\t    <code>Puzzle</code> contract exposed at <a href=\"/openapi\">/openapi</a>.</p>\n128\t  </article>\n129\t\n130\t  <footer class=\"site\">\n131\t    ${escapeHtml(app)} · <a href=\"/openapi\">API</a> · <a href=\"/openapi.json\">openapi.json</a>\n132\t    · build ${escapeHtml(version)}\n133\t  </footer>\n134\t</main>\n135\t<script>\n136\t${AUTH_CHIP_SCRIPT}\n137\t</script>\n138\t</body>\n139\t</html>`;\n140\t}\n141\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea97c4a2-67f7-4ff7-8c74-f9bccb4cced2","uuid":"eeebd2e2-8024-4570-80f9-22603b6feeec","timestamp":"2026-06-17T12:34:39.795Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/data/work/worker-plat-timealign-initial-mqi1ilmpq/src/homepage.ts","content":"// The landing page served at / — framed as a short Wikipedia-style article: a\n// lead paragraph, a catalogue infobox, a brief \"How to play\" block, and the\n// puzzle picker as a dense, scannable table. Puzzle summaries are rendered\n// server-side (no client fetch, no loading flash); the only client JS is the\n// auth chip in the body header.\nimport type { PuzzleSummary } from \"./puzzles.js\";\nimport {\n  AUTH_CHIP_SCRIPT,\n  authChip,\n  bodyHeader,\n  escapeHtml,\n  PAGE_CSS,\n  pageHeader,\n} from \"./ui.js\";\n\nconst DIFFICULTY_LABEL: Record<string, string> = {\n  easy: \"Easy\",\n  medium: \"Medium\",\n  hard: \"Hard\",\n};\n\n// Pull every 4-digit year out of the catalogue's per-puzzle span strings\n// (\"1776–2007\", \"2001\", …) so the infobox can report the overall coverage.\nfunction catalogueYears(puzzles: PuzzleSummary[]): number[] {\n  return puzzles\n    .flatMap((p) => p.span.split(/[^0-9]+/))\n    .filter(Boolean)\n    .map(Number);\n}\n\nexport function homepage({\n  app,\n  version,\n  puzzles,\n}: {\n  app: string;\n  version: string;\n  puzzles: PuzzleSummary[];\n}): string {\n  const totalEvents = puzzles.reduce((n, p) => n + p.eventCount, 0);\n  const years = catalogueYears(puzzles);\n  const overallSpan = years.length\n    ? `${Math.min(...years)}–${Math.max(...years)}`\n    : \"—\";\n  // Difficulties present, in canonical order, for the infobox range.\n  const order = [\"easy\", \"medium\", \"hard\"];\n  const diffs = order.filter((d) => puzzles.some((p) => p.difficulty === d));\n  const diffRange = diffs.map((d) => DIFFICULTY_LABEL[d] ?? d).join(\" – \");\n\n  const rows = puzzles\n    .map((p) => {\n      const label = DIFFICULTY_LABEL[p.difficulty] ?? p.difficulty;\n      const theme = p.theme ?? \"Mixed events\";\n      return `\n      <tr>\n        <td><a href=\"/play/${escapeHtml(p.id)}\">${escapeHtml(theme)}</a></td>\n        <td>${escapeHtml(label)}</td>\n        <td>${p.eventCount}</td>\n        <td>${escapeHtml(p.span)}</td>\n      </tr>`;\n    })\n    .join(\"\");\n\n  return `<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\">\n<title>${escapeHtml(app)} — a history timeline placement game</title>\n<style>\n${PAGE_CSS}\n  .infobox.cat{float:right;width:290px;max-width:46%;margin:.2rem 0 1rem 1.5rem}\n  @media(max-width:640px){.infobox.cat{float:none;width:auto;max-width:none;margin:1rem 0}}\n  .howto{margin:.4rem 0 0}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n${pageHeader()}\n${bodyHeader({\n  left: \"A history timeline placement game\",\n  right: `<a href=\"/openapi\">API</a>${authChip()}`,\n})}\n\n<main class=\"wrap\">\n  <article>\n    <aside class=\"infobox cat\" aria-label=\"Catalogue summary\">\n      <div class=\"ib-title\">${escapeHtml(app)}</div>\n      <table>\n        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Puzzles</th><td>${puzzles.length}</td></tr>\n        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Events</th><td>${totalEvents}</td></tr>\n        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Span</th><td>${escapeHtml(overallSpan)}</td></tr>\n        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Difficulty</th><td>${escapeHtml(diffRange || \"—\")}</td></tr>\n        <tr><th scope=\"row\">Source</th><td>Hand-authored, Wikipedia</td></tr>\n      </table>\n    </aside>\n\n    <p class=\"lead\">You are shown a historical event with its date hidden, and you\n    slot it onto a shared timeline — before, after, or between the events already\n    placed. Commit to reveal the real date, score the guess, and read more on\n    Wikipedia. It is played in the spirit of the board game <i>Timeline</i>.</p>\n\n    <h2 id=\"how-to-play\">How to play</h2>\n    <ol class=\"howto\">\n      <li>Pick a puzzle from the table below.</li>\n      <li>The board opens with one anchor event already placed and dated. Earlier\n      events sit toward the top, later events toward the bottom.</li>\n      <li>You are handed the rest one at a time, date hidden. Tap a marked gap, then\n      tap Commit.</li>\n      <li>Commit reveals the date. Correct earns 100 points plus a 25-point streak\n      bonus per consecutive hit; wrong scores nothing and snaps into place. Either\n      way the timeline stays in order.</li>\n    </ol>\n\n    <h2 id=\"puzzles\">Puzzles</h2>\n    <table class=\"wikitable\">\n      <thead>\n        <tr><th scope=\"col\">Puzzle</th><th scope=\"col\">Difficulty</th>\n            <th scope=\"col\">Events</th><th scope=\"col\">Years</th></tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tbody>\n        ${rows}\n      </tbody>\n    </table>\n\n    <p>This demo ships ${puzzles.length} hand-authored puzzles. The roadmap is puzzles\n    generated on demand from Wikidata and Wikipedia, emitted against the same typed\n    <code>Puzzle</code> contract exposed at <a href=\"/openapi\">/openapi</a>.</p>\n  </article>\n\n  <footer class=\"site\">\n    ${escapeHtml(app)} · <a href=\"/openapi\">API</a> · <a href=\"/openapi.json\">openapi.json</a>\n    · build ${escapeHtml(version)}\n  </footer>\n</main>\n<script>\n${AUTH_CHIP_SCRIPT}\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>`;\n}\n","numLines":141,"startLine":1,"totalLines":141}}}
