{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011B2McTYJcraYsyMH923sWx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LVKP8en6519cTAx9BJzVBd","name":"mcp__plat__update_issue","input":{"owner":"plat","name":"timealign-initial","number":5,"title":"Content-first, Wikipedia-style design foundation","body":"Closes #4\n\nEstablishes a single **content-first, Wikipedia-style design system** in `src/ui.ts` that every page composes from, and reworks the homepage, game board, and 404 on top of it. The game engine is untouched. This PR incorporates all four follow-up requests from review.\n\n## What changed\n\n- **One shared design system (`src/ui.ts`).** Tokens + reset, the page header, the Wikipedia-style body header, the infobox/`wikitable` styles, and the auth chip all live in one place so the pages can't drift apart.\n- **Two typefaces only** — Linux Libertine for section titles, Helvetica for everything else.\n- **All text is black; the only colour is hyperlink blue.** No custom palette, no decorative borders, no all-caps labels — just thin Wikipedia rules, tables, and infoboxes. *(The one deliberate exception: the game board keeps a single functional green/red for transient correct/wrong placement feedback — that is game state, not decoration.)*\n- **Header split into two parts, Wikipedia-style:**\n  - **Page header** — just the page title (*Timelines Demo*) and, on sub-pages, a back arrow. Nothing else.\n  - **Body header** — two thin horizontal rules at content width, with utility info between them (left-aligned context, right-aligned links + the auth chip). Present on **every** page.\n- **Auth chip is now a shared component** rendered in the body header on every page, including the 404 — fixing the earlier nit where `/play/<unknown-id>` showed no identity.\n- **Game board timeline** sits in its own **rectangular bordered container**, so its width stays constant as it grows (no more wrapping around a floated element).\n- **Homepage** reads as a short article: lead paragraph, catalogue infobox, \"How to play\" block, and the puzzle picker as a dense `wikitable`.\n- **README** updated to describe the shipped design exactly.\n\n## How it was verified\n\n`npm run lint`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build` all pass; CI `check` is green.\n\nDrove the live preview (`https://pr-5-timealign-initial-plat.plat.local`) with Playwright:\n\n- **Homepage** — minimal page header (just *Timelines Demo*), body header with left context + right links/auth chip between two rules, catalogue infobox (4 puzzles · 27 events · 1776–2018 · Easy–Hard) and the `wikitable` picker all render correctly.\n- **Game board** (*Turning Points in World History*) — minimal page header (back arrow + title), body header with score + auth chip, metadata caption, and the timeline in its own rectangular container. Played a round: placed *Hiroshima* after the Titanic anchor → Commit revealed *August 6, 1945*, Score 100 · Streak 1, next card dealt. Engine fully intact; the container grows without shifting width.\n- **404** (`/play/does-not-exist`) — same page header + body header, and the **auth chip now renders** here (shows *Sign in* while signed out) — the earlier nit is fixed. Puzzle id is HTML-escaped.\n- **Console** — only the pre-existing benign noise (anonymous `/api/me` 401, missing favicon); no errors introduced by this change.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":483,"cache_read_input_tokens":67601,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":483},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea97c4a2-67f7-4ff7-8c74-f9bccb4cced2","uuid":"99bc9c82-7d97-415e-a3ca-86e6d4bd3b9c","request_id":"req_011Cc8qrGfGyodxFvVUNYaqN"}
